offertory.lyrics:
Take, O Take Me As I Am,
Recreate The Heart Of Clay;
Shape A New Life In Your Pattern,
Word Of God, I Humbly Pray.

Summon Out Whom I Should Serve;
Give Me Courage, Strength And Nerve;
Bid Me Act The Love I Praise,
All My Busy, Bustling Days.

Take The Work My Hands Can Offer;
Take The Loaves, The Work Of Art;
Take Myself—each Part I Proffer—
Take, O Lord, My Broken Heart.

Take My Life As Wine Outpoured:
Drink From The Fruit Of Every Field.
Take My Love—i Am Your Harp,
Take My Song, Let Your Tune Be Heard.

Take, O Take Me As I Am,
Recreate The Heart Of Clay;
Shape A New Life In Your Pattern,
God Of Love, I Humbly Pray.

Praise God, From Whom All Blessings Flow;
Praise Him, All Creatures Here Below;
Praise Him Above, Ye Heavenly Host;
Praise Father, Son, And Holy Ghost. Amen.

Let Earth And Heaven Adore His Name,
And Every Heart His Grace Proclaim;
With Grateful Songs And Lifted Voice,
We Bless The Lord And Now Rejoice.

recessional.lyrics:
God Of Our Fathers, Whose Almighty Hand
Leads Forth In Beauty All The Starry Band
Of Shining Worlds In Splendor Through The Skies:
Our Grateful Songs Before Your Throne Arise.

Your Love Divine Has Led Us In The Past;
In This Free Land By You Our Lot Is Cast;
You Are Our Ruler, Guardian, Guide, And Stay;
Your Word Our Law, Your Paths Our Chosen Way.

Refresh Your People On Their Toilsome Way,
Lead Us From Night To Never-ending Day;
Fill All Our Lives With Heaven-born Love And Grace
Until At Last We Meet Before Your Face.
